   System Flowchart
The following describes the overall flow of the Employee Attendance System. The
flowchart diagram has been created and saved in the Flowcharts folder of the FitHub repository.
The system follows this general flow:
1. START- The program begins execution.
2. MAIN MENU- The user is presented with the following options:
• 1- Add Employee Record
• 2- Search Employee Record
• 3- Display All Records
• 4- Update Attendance Status
• 5- Exit Program
￼ 6
3. ADD RECORD- The user enters an Employee ID, Employee Name and Attendance
Status. The system validates the input and adds the record to the array. A confirmation
message is displayed.
4. SEARCH RECORD- The user enters an Employee ID or Employee Name. The
system searches the records and displays the matching employee information or an
error message if not found.
5. DISPLAY RECORDS- Te system displays all current employee attendance records in
a formatted table.
6. UPDATE STATUS- The user enters the Employee ID and a new Attendance Status.
The system locates the record and updates the status. A confirmation message is
displayed.
7. GENERATE SUMMARY REPORT- The system calculates and displays the total
number of employees, the number of employees Present, the number of employees
Absent, and the number of employees on Leave.
8. EXIT PROGRAM- The program terminates and a farewell message is displayed.
Program Structure
The following major dictions have been identified for future software implementation.
These functions correspond directly to the system flowchart and the main menu options.
￼ 7
Function Name Description
add_record() Prompts the user to enter Employee ID, Name, and Attendance Status.
Validates input and adds the record to system array.
search_record() Accepts a search term (Employee ID or Name) and returns the matching
employee record or an error message if not found.
display_records() Iterates through all stores records and displays them in a formatted,
relatable layout.
update_status() Locates an employee record by ID and updates the attendance status to a
new below provided by the user.
generate_report() Calculates and displays a summary of total employees, present count,
absent count, and on-leave count.
main_menu() Displays the main menu options and routes the user to the selected
function.
